1.2
log
@Drop patch; not needed anymore since the recent FAKE_AS_ROOT fix.
@
text
@$OpenBSD: patch-make_ptbuildopts_mak_in,v 1.1 2014/08/25 07:05:46 ajacoutot Exp $

INSTALL is forcibly set to ${WRKBUILD}/bin/install:
    ${WRKBUILD}/bin/install -> /usr/bin/install
which break builds of dependant ports (e.g. h323plus)

--- make/ptbuildopts.mak.in.orig	Mon Aug 25 08:47:55 2014
+++ make/ptbuildopts.mak.in	Mon Aug 25 08:48:05 2014
@@@@ -16,7 +16,9 @@@@ PTLIB_PLUGIN_DIR := @@PTLIB_PLUGIN_DIR@@
 AR	:= @@AR@@
 CC	:= @@CC@@
 CXX	:= @@CXX@@
+ifndef INSTALL
 INSTALL := @@INSTALL@@
+endif
 SVN     := @@SVN@@
 BISON   := @@BISON@@
 
@


1.1
log
@Do not re-define INSTALL otherwise we end up using the one from ${WRKBUILD}.
This unbreaks dependant ports like h323plus.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
$OpenBSD$
